main event: A civilian in Fonculac, Minnesota reported seeing a large, cigar-shaped object with red, green, and white lights in the sky for about 15 minutes on August 17, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as being 60 to 70 feet in wingspan, silvery in color, and emitting a fluorescent glow.
The object did not appear to have any portholes or exhaust, and made no sound.
The object initially moved towards the horizon, then remained stationary as the observers watched from below.
The sighting occurred at dusk, and the observers noted only a few thin clouds in the sky at the time.
There was no significant temperature inversion or astronomical activity reported in the area at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: large, cigar-shaped object with red, green, and white lights
witnesses: Rowland Redstennin, his wife Elaine, and their daughters Bonnie and Lana
